-- Siemens Gets 150-Megawatt Wind Turbine Order in Canada
-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 2013-10-08T18:20:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-08/siemens-gets-150-megawatt-wind-turbine-order-in-canada.html
Siemens AG (SIE) , Europe’s biggest
engineering company, agreed to provide about 150 megawatts of
wind turbines for a power project in  Canada .  Samsung C&T Corp. (000830) ’s Canadian renewables unit and Pattern
Energy Group LP will install 67 of Siemens’s 2.3-megawatt
turbines as part of the Grand Renewable Energy Park that will
also have 100 megawatts of solar panels, Munich-based Siemens
said today in a statement. Terms weren’t disclosed.  The plant in Haldimand County, Ontario, is the second
Samsung and Pattern are building with Siemens equipment. They
are also developing the 270-megawatt South Kent Wind project in
Chatham-Kent County that will go into operation in the first
quarter. Power from both will be sold to Ontario Power
Authority.  To contact the reporter on this story:
